          "name": "items",
          "role": "exclusive questions and answers",
          "contract": "faq-item",
          "width": "full",
          "z": "front",
          "copy": [
            {
              "question": "Do we have to move every country at once?",
              "answer": "No. The plan groups countries by readiness, risk, calendar, and contract timing. Most teams start with a clean cohort and reuse that operating pattern for the next group."
            },
            {
              "question": "Can we keep our existing HR system?",
              "answer": "Yes. The goal is to consolidate the payroll operating layer, not force every people workflow into a new tool. The assessment records which systems stay and where data needs a dependable handoff."
            },
            {
              "question": "What happens to our local payroll providers?",
              "answer": "The plan makes that decision country by country. It identifies which relationships should end, which obligations need a controlled transition, and where a phased handover reduces risk."
            },
            {
              "question": "Who needs to join the assessment?",
              "answer": "Usually payroll, finance, people operations, and the owner of your HR data. We keep the working group small and bring in local stakeholders only where a country decision needs them."
            },
            {
              "question": "What do we receive at the end?",
              "answer": "A country map, recommended operating model, migration cohorts, control owners, and the decisions required before the first consolidated payroll run."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
